node.text:
I will never get tired of sharing Mary’s story. 💙 She’s a refugee from South Sudan, a powerful advocate for education, a TED speaker and a theatre student.

For #WorldRefugeeDay, please watch this film as she and I play a little game to talk about what home means to us - with some very special heirlooms - and why getting an education is so important for all refugees.

There’s so much I could say about this incredible woman - but she can tell you herself. Keep an eye on my Instagram Stories today where she’ll be showing you all a glimpse of her life in Minnesota, and her dreams and goals for the future. You can follow her at @marymaker_43 - and please head to @refugees to see and hear more incredible stories like hers. Thank you. 

#WithRefugees

I am so honored and grateful to be named a United Nations Goodwill Ambassador for UNHCR, The UN Refugee Agency. 

The refugees I’ve met over the years have inspired me through their strength, resilience and incredible capabilities to teach and help support their communities.

I’m proud to support @refugees who work tirelessly every day to help ensure that the millions of people who have been forced to flee their homes, leaving behind all they’ve known or had... are able to live in safety and with dignity. Please join me on this journey and give them hope. Link in my bio. 

#WithRefugees

node.text: Rita is the first refugee yoga teacher in Kenya’s Kakuma camp. She’s using the power of yoga to bring wellness and healing to both refugees and humanitarian workers with her classes – now online because of COVID-19 restrictions. Rita’s practice focuses on messages of self-acceptance and mental well-being. On this #WorldMentalHealthDay we all must realize that mental health support should be a right, not a luxury, for @refugees, the humanitarians supporting them, and everyone else. #WithRefugees 🙏🏽❤️ @refugees

node.text:
When I saw this video that @refugees just posted I wanted to share it with you guys as quickly as possible (thanks @danamhughes 🙏🏽🙌🏽). Uganda has a history of being kind to refugees. I witnessed it firsthand when I visited a @refugees camp last year.

This week Uganda opened up its borders to thousands of desperate refugees seeking a safe haven after fleeing horrific violence in the Democratic Republic of Congo. Mostly women and children had been stranded in a remote, inaccessible area, living for weeks without food or water.
 
Uganda is a great example to the world, showing how even during #COVID19 we can still find ways to safely welcome those in need.  Thankful for @refugees staff like @duniyaakhan who are there on the frontlines working with governments and supporting the many people who still have no choice but to flee their homes, even in this challenging time. 

If you guys can donate, even one dollar, the link is in my bio. 

#WithRefugees #EveryActionCounts #Uganda

@kyletekiela @ctcmovie @shameikmoore @dshippjr @blackmouf @eizagonzalez @theterrencehoward @ethanhawke @realwesleysnipes @rumbleriot @wellgousa LET’S GO!!! The distributors have committed to donating a portion of the film’s proceeds to lowernine.org, a nonprofit organization dedicated to the long-term recovery of New Orleans’ historic Lower Ninth Ward. 🙌🏽 Original song by @wutangclan #CutThroatCity

node.text: Life was so tough for the Syrian refugee families I met when I visited the camp in Jordan in 2014, so I could not imagine how much harder COVID-19 has made their lives. That’s why ahead of #WorldRefugee Day I connected with Irene, the camp manager for Za’atari, which now houses nearly 80,000 refugees. This inspiring woman is truly committed to working for and standing with @refugees, even in the face of a global pandemic. After learning three months ago that that Za’atari was going to be locked down due to coronavirus, Irene packed a bag and moved to the camp. She wanted to make sure she could stay close to the refugees she serves. Irene is the true definition of a humanitarian. But you don’t have to work at UNHCR or be a hero to stand in solidarity with refugees. Everyone can help make a difference. Every action counts. Please watch and click the link in my bio to find out more. #RefugeeDay #WithRefugees

I am truly grateful to everyone who joined @felaridi @ikarwood and I at this year’s @Modern.Nirvana conference. 

I learned so much more of what it means to be of service to humanity. To join hands and walk towards wellness together… to run towards it. 

Honoring the man that has been my spiritual north star since I was 12 years old and now one my closest friends and mentors, @DeepakChopra with the consciousness award, has truly been a blessing. From quantum physics to space and time, UDB!!!! I love you my friend. Thank you for giving us this honor. 

Thank you @DaveAspery for teaching me humor, humility and taking more control of my nutrition. You speak from such a grounded and humble space yet drop so much wisdom, it’s hard to comprehend the same guy cracking jokes in the cowboy hat with us is the titan behind @bulletproof!

Thank you to Michael and Ylianna @heartwater for building this with us. The journey is only beginning!!! I can’t wait to shout off of every mountain top how much I love you guys and our water and how IT IS THE FUTURE OF WATER!!!!! You are my family now and always. One day I will share the “coincidences” behind our divine connection with the world. 💜

Thank you @Roi33 @polisg @angelleconsulting @ale_ssiofilippelli the @musichillatx team, team @heartwater and team Palmer for helping us pull this off! We could not have done it without you!!! And thank you to my lovey @dijonnaise911 for holding me down energetically thru one of the toughest months ever. Thank you 🙏🏽.

And thank YOU guys for all that you gave by coming and sharing your time. Thank you for all that you’ve taught me. The constant kindness you give me. The unwavering support and profound love... I hope that I’m a reflection of that love back at you. I hope that at Modern Nirvana we can continue to be of service to any and everyone looking to find their ultimate truths and highest awakenings. 

And so the journey to our best selves continues…

❤️🙏🏽

node.text: As the fight against the COVID-19 pandemic continues, these @refugees are helping make their community a safer place. I had the privilege of meeting with Dr. Omar Aziz and his team to hear their inspiring stories and see first-hand the lifesaving work they do. Thanks to their efforts, over 7,000 vaccinations have been administered throughout DeKalb County, Georgia and they have brought needed medical resources to those most in need. They are the living proof that our country is made stronger when we welcome newcomers, especially the most vulnerable people who have been displaced and forced to flee.  #WithRefugees #Covid19 #Vaccine @refugees @ircatlanta @core_georgia
